		<title>Bust Your Slump</title>
		<link>http://blog.salesopedia.com/?p=4711</link>
		<comments>http://blog.salesopedia.com/?p=4711#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sat, 27 Nov 2010 22:44:04 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Editor</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Podcasts]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Paul McCord]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[sales slump]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.salesopedia.com/?p=4711</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Paul McCord just released a book Bust Your Slump. He shares some of the content from the book. Paul believe sales slumps happen because of several factors, it is not the lack of activity alone. Negative expectations can often be a major variable that can keep you in a rut. ]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>Paul McCord</strong> just released a book <a href="http://www.bustyourslump.com" target=new>Bust Your Slump</a>. He shares some of the content from the book. Paul believe sales slumps happen because of several factors, it is not the lack of activity alone. Negative expectations can often be a major variable that can keep you in a rut. Paul talks about marketing ideas and action items designed to create quick sales. In his book he addresses 12 ideas; in this podcast he reviews a few suggestions go put sales in your pipeline and money in your pocket. </p>
<p>Paul McCord a globally recognized expert in prospecting, business development, and personal marketing. Paul has more than three decades experience selling and leading top sales teams. He founded McCord Training to help companies and sellers excel by developing strategies and techniques that prospects accept, respect and respond to. </p>
]]></content:encoded>
